Zomato is an Indian multinational company founded in 2008 that operates as a leading platform for food delivery and restaurant discovery. It was started by **Deepinder Goyal** and **Pankaj Chaddah**, initially under the name *Foodiebay*, before being rebranded as Zomato in 2010.

The company provides a range of services including online food ordering and delivery, restaurant search and reviews, table reservations, and subscription programs like Zomato Gold (now Zomato Pro). It also operates in multiple countries, although its primary market is India. Over time, Zomato has expanded into quick commerce through Blinkit, offering fast delivery of groceries and essentials.

Zomato generates revenue through delivery commissions, restaurant advertising, subscription services, and logistics support, positioning itself as a key player in India’s rapidly growing food-tech and online delivery ecosystem.

